<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-169-140 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 650 624</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  April 30 1991 v5 n17 p1(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Macweek 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>System 7.0 going golden, but first run will be limited. (Apple torelease System 7.0 system software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Guglielmo, Connie.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Apple will release the long-awaited System 7.0 operating systemfor the Macintosh on May 13, 1991, but volume shipments are notexpected until late May or early June.andP;  Developers at Apple havenot yet created a 'golden' master copy of System 7.0 fordistribution, but the software will reportedly be 'frozen' theweek of Apr 29 and duplicated in limited quantities fordistribution at the official rollout.andP;  Apple may make System 7.0immediately available though user groups, reversing earlier plans.andO;Upgrade kits will cost $99 for a single user or $349 for a workgroup; those who obtain the software on-line can obtain a packageof 15 user manuals for $249.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   System 7.0 (Operating system) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Operating SystemsSystems SoftwareProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Connie GuglielmoandM;Cupertino, Calif.andP;  -- Apple last week put to rest any lingering fears thatSystem 7.0 will not be released May 13 -- not by settling on a final versionof the new operating system, but by distributing the official System 7T-shirt.andM;Apple currently has several near-final versions of the system, called finalcandidates, one of which is destined to be selected as the basis for theSystem 7.0 &quot;golden master,&quot; according to sources.andM;Apple engineers have been scrambling to track down and fix a variety ofcompatibility problems and mostly minor bugs reported in recent weeks bydevelopers, who have been testing various near-final versions since March.andM;As of late last week, Apple developers were working with versions labeledSystem 7.0f3 and System 7.0f4, but they had not yet created a golden master.andO;According to sources, however, the company plans to freeze the software thisweek and begin duplicating floppies and CD-ROMs to create limited quantitiesfor distribution at the May 13 rollout.andM;Because of manufacturing and ramp-up time, System 7.0 will not reachresellers in quantity until late May or early June, sources said.andP;  Apple,however, reportedly has reversed earlier plans and now intends to make System7.0 immediately available through user groups.andP;  Several groups have receivedletters from Apple encouraging them to sign up for a free license that willallow them to copy and distribute the operating system.andM;The company also plans to distribute the system via on-line services, as ithas done with other systems in the past, sources added.andM;To accommodate those who do not purchase either the $99 single-user or $349group upgrade kit (see MacWEEK, April 23), Apple will offer a package of 15user manuals for $249.andM;System 7.0 T-shirts, which were mailed along with invitations to the May 13debut, list the new operating system with other notable sevens -- the sevendeadly sins, the seven voyages of Sinbad, and Snow White and the sevendwarfs.andM;Industry pundit Guy Kawasaki added that seven also is a significant numberwhen playing dice, but cautioned Mac users to remember that &quot;Seven is a luckynumber only on the first roll.&quot;andO;</TEXT></DOC>